abstract: “Trump’s like a mobster who instead of throwing a body in the trunk, throws it in the passenger seat so he can use the car pool lane,” Meyers said Thursday.

headline_main: Impeachment, Brexit, French Police: Your Friday Briefing

abstract: The vice president has risen to his boss’s defense at a moment of crisis that some Republicans fear could inflict lasting damage on them both.
snippet: The vice president has risen to his boss’s defense at a moment of crisis that some Republicans fear could inflict lasting damage on them both.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — He held firm when the “Access Hollywood” tape nearly ended President Trump’s 2016 campaign. He did not waver through even the most trying moments of the special counsel’s Russia investigation.

abstract: Without presenting any evidence, President Trump suggested that China showered money on Mr. Biden to influence his father as vice president and win favorable trade deals with the United States.
snippet: Without presenting any evidence, President Trump suggested that China showered money on Mr. Biden to influence his father as vice president and win favorable trade deals with the United States.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s latest broadside against former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and his son Hunter appears to center on a joint venture that involved the younger Mr. Biden and some of China’s leading state-owned financial companies.

abstract: Two American diplomats drafted a statement for Ukraine’s new leader that would have committed him publicly to the inquiries Mr. Trump has been seeking into political rivals.
snippet: Two American diplomats drafted a statement for Ukraine’s new leader that would have committed him publicly to the inquiries Mr. Trump has been seeking into political rivals.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Two of President Trump’s top envoys to Ukraine worked on a statement for the country’s new president in August that would have committed Ukraine to pursuing investigations sought by Mr. Trump into his political rivals, according to three people briefed on the effort and documents released Thursday night.

snippet: The sum was $7 million less than Mr. Biden’s fund-raising haul in the previous quarter.
lead_paragraph: Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has raised $15.2 million in the past three months, his campaign said Thursday, a drop-off of $7 million from the previous quarter and a sum that falls short of two leading Democratic rivals.
